author: KIRO 7 STAFF
title: Snohomish Co. Sheriff: Teen mother found, infant still missing
text:
Detectives continue to search for a newborn baby after her missing mother was found in South Everett on Monday.
The two disappeared after the 16-year-old parent gave birth to the child without medical observation between Sept. 10 and Sept. 18, according to the Snohomish County sheriff.
A Snohomish County sheriff's spokeswoman sent a news release on Oct. 1 about the two disappearing, writing the mother, Leah Lund, may be transient. Details have been limited about Lund being found on Monday.
The infant is considered endangered because of lack of medical care and her mother's alleged heroin use.
Missing teen, Leah Lund, was located today around 2 p.m. in S Everett. Detectives still searching for her baby. http://t.co/sJZCGsTe3X
